2026-04-16 12:16:37 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 3 switch contacts / internal 12V path'] hypothesis_explanation='Voltage tracing shows ~12 V present correctly up to the output of Control Module 2, and 0 V already at the *input* of Control Module 3’s output side (Control Output Cable (+) 3). This indicates that somewhere between CM3’s input 12 V terminal and its output 12 V terminal the series path is open, while all wiring up to CM2 is sound and no polarity inversion is present. Since the design of each control module is simply a switch in series with the 12 V line, an open or failed switch contact (or an open internal trace/connection in the 12 V path) inside Control Module 3 would cause exactly this behavior: all downstream modules, including the load, see 0 V, none of their indicators can light, and the upstream supply LED remains on. Therefore the most probable single fault is an internal open in Control Module 3’s series 12 V path (including its switch), and that module should be repaired or replaced.'
